{
  "id": "RAW_66ebc160",
  "title": "Vercel：反供应商锁定的云平台 - Vercel",
  "url": "https://vercel.com/blog/vercel-the-anti-vendor-lock-in-cloud",
  "date": "2025-11-10 13:00:00",
  "author": "Malte Ubl, Tom Occhino, Kevin Corbett",
  "siteName": "Vercel News",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div class=\"stack-module__UbbKhW__stack stack article-module__9eLiuW__content\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:column;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:24px\" data-customer-story=\"false\" data-contentful-locale=\"en-US\" data-contentful-field-id=\"content\" data-contentful-entry-id=\"4TCxTuww8eSvSx3CA0exA6\">\n   <div class=\"stack-module__UbbKhW__stack stack w-full flex-wrap gap-4 pt-2\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:row;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:space-between;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\">\n    <div class=\"stack-module__UbbKhW__stack stack\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:row;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:flex-start;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:6px\">\n     <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--text-size:0.875rem;--text-line-height:1.25rem;--text-letter-spacing:0px;--text-weight:400\"><span style=\"background-color: inherit; font-size: 1rem;\">Vendor lock-in matters when choosing a cloud platform. Cloud platforms can lock you in by requiring you to build against their specific primitives. Vercel takes a different approach: you write code for your framework, not for Vercel.</span></p>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"stack-module__UbbKhW__stack stack w-full flex-wrap gap-6\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--stack-flex:initial;--stack-direction:row;--stack-align:center;--stack-justify:space-between;--stack-padding:0px;--stack-gap:0px\" data-contentful-locale=\"en-US\" data-contentful-field-id=\"intro\" data-contentful-entry-id=\"4TCxTuww8eSvSx3CA0exA6\">\n    <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">On AWS, you configure Lambda functions, NAT Gateways, and DynamoDB tables. On Cloudflare, you write Workers, use KV stores, Durable Objects, and bind services with Worker Service Bindings. These primitives only exist with that vendor, which means migrating to another platform requires rewriting your application architecture.</p>\n    <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Too often, cloud platforms make these choices for you. They define proprietary primitives, APIs, and services that pull your code deeper into their ecosystem until leaving becomes impractical.</p>\n    <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">At Vercel, we believe the opposite approach creates better software and a healthier web. We want developers to stay because they want to, not because they have to. That means building open tools, embracing standards, and ensuring your code remains portable no matter where it runs.</p>\n    <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">So Vercel works differently. It interprets your framework code and provisions infrastructure automatically. Your application does not need to know it runs on Vercel. You do not need to import Vercel modules or call Vercel APIs. This is <a target=\"_self\" data-zone=\"same\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight\" href=\"https://vercel.com/blog/framework-defined-infrastructure\">framework-defined infrastructure</a>.</p>\n   </div>\n   <h2 class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1.5rem;--xs-text-line-height:2rem;--xs-text-weight:600;--xs-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--sm-text-size:1.5rem;--sm-text-line-height:2rem;--sm-text-weight:600;--sm-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--smd-text-size:2rem;--smd-text-line-height:2.5rem;--smd-text-weight:600;--smd-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--md-text-size:2rem;--md-text-line-height:2.5rem;--md-text-weight:600;--md-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--lg-text-size:2rem;--lg-text-line-height:2.5rem;--lg-text-weight:600;--lg-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#what-vendor-lock-in-actually-means\" id=\"what-vendor-lock-in-actually-means\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>What vendor lock-in actually means</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Vendor lock-in happens when a platform builds features that deviate from open standards, which are accessed in your application code via proprietary APIs. If your application uses those features, you cannot move to another platform without rewriting code.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">When you build against vendor primitives like AWS Step Functions or Cloudflare Durable Objects, those dependencies live in your application code. Your business logic ties to platform APIs, which means moving requires rewriting that logic to work with different primitives.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Framework conventions like the Next.js App Router, Remix loaders, SvelteKit endpoints, and Nitro storage adapters work differently. You build against the framework, not the platform. Multiple platforms can run the same framework code, keeping your application portable across any infrastructure that supports it.</p>\n   <div class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 max-w-none mt-20 mb-10 mx-0 max-[600px]:max-w-none max-[600px]:w-full max-[600px]:mt-12 max-[600px]:mb-6\">\n    <img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"Framework-defined Infrastructure means developers define infrastructure through their framework, not through vendor-specific code or logic.\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"647\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image-module__ssnYEW__intrinsic blog-mode-dependent-media-module__HJT-FW__addPadding blog-mode-dependent-media-module__HJT-FW__notScreenshot image-module__ssnYEW__lightMode\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcset=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F4BNYrHEm0rcFhgHVp6kwbA%2F90ed98ff3d469b8c881232adac8a4c10%2FFDI.png&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1x, https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F4BNYrHEm0rcFhgHVp6kwbA%2F90ed98ff3d469b8c881232adac8a4c10%2FFDI.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F4BNYrHEm0rcFhgHVp6kwbA%2F90ed98ff3d469b8c881232adac8a4c10%2FFDI.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\">\n    <figcaption class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper m-auto max-w-[var(--article-max-width)] max-[600px]:px-0 max-[600px]:py-4\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-900);--text-size:0.875rem;--text-line-height:1.25rem;--text-letter-spacing:initial;--text-weight:400;--text-align:center\">Framework-defined Infrastructure means developers define infrastructure through their framework, not through vendor-specific code or logic.</figcaption>\n   </div>\n   <h2 class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1.5rem;--xs-text-line-height:2rem;--xs-text-weight:600;--xs-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--sm-text-size:1.5rem;--sm-text-line-height:2rem;--sm-text-weight:600;--sm-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--smd-text-size:2rem;--smd-text-line-height:2.5rem;--smd-text-weight:600;--smd-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--md-text-size:2rem;--md-text-line-height:2.5rem;--md-text-weight:600;--md-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--lg-text-size:2rem;--lg-text-line-height:2.5rem;--lg-text-weight:600;--lg-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#framework-defined-infrastructure-means-portable-code\" id=\"framework-defined-infrastructure-means-portable-code\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Framework-defined infrastructure means portable code</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">This portability is possible because of framework-defined infrastructure (FDI). FDI means that the platform reads your code and determines what infrastructure you need. You follow your framework's patterns, Vercel handles the rest.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Complex production applications run on Vercel without mentioning <code>vercel</code> anywhere in their codebase. They follow Next.js conventions (or Remix, SvelteKit, Nuxt, or one of 40+ supported frameworks). Vercel analyzes the build output and provisions middleware, functions, static assets, and caching accordingly.</p>\n   <h3 class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper relative group w-full pt-6 text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:600;--xs-text-letter-spacing:-0.32px;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:600;--sm-text-letter-spacing:-0.32px;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:600;--smd-text-letter-spacing:-0.32px;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:600;--md-text-letter-spacing:-0.32px;--lg-text-size:1.25rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.625rem;--lg-text-weight:600;--lg-text-letter-spacing:-0.4px\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#local-development-requires-no-vercel-tooling\" id=\"local-development-requires-no-vercel-tooling\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"width:12px;height:12px;color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Local development requires no Vercel tooling</h3>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Platforms built on vendor primitives need complex simulators for local development. Cloudflare provides Wrangler to simulate Workers locally. AWS developers use LocalStack or SAM CLI to mock Lambda and other services. These tools approximate production behavior but never match it exactly.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">With FDI, you run your framework's standard development server. For Next.js, run <code>next dev</code>. For Remix, <code>remix dev</code>. The code you write runs the same way locally and in production. There's no Vercel CLI to install and no simulation layer creating differences between environments.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">This architectural choice has a direct impact on portability. When you write against framework standards instead of platform primitives, your code can run elsewhere without modification.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1.5rem;--xs-text-line-height:2rem;--xs-text-weight:600;--xs-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--sm-text-size:1.5rem;--sm-text-line-height:2rem;--sm-text-weight:600;--sm-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--smd-text-size:2rem;--smd-text-line-height:2.5rem;--smd-text-weight:600;--smd-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--md-text-size:2rem;--md-text-line-height:2.5rem;--md-text-weight:600;--md-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--lg-text-size:2rem;--lg-text-line-height:2.5rem;--lg-text-weight:600;--lg-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#most-next.js-apps-already-run-outside-of-vercel\" id=\"most-next.js-apps-already-run-outside-of-vercel\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Most Next.js apps already run outside of Vercel</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Next.js is the most widely deployed framework on Vercel. Because of this, some might assume that this creates lock-in, but the data shows otherwise.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Based on Next.js telemetry tracking distinct projects, approximately 70% of Next.js applications run outside of Vercel. This also likely undercounts non-Vercel deployments because Vercel deployments rarely disable telemetry, while self-hosted deployments often opt out and won't appear in the data.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Many companies currently self-host Next.js on their own infrastructure, proving this portability in practice. Walmart.com serves millions of shoppers daily on self-hosted Next.js, Nike.com operates at global scale on their own systems, and Claude.ai also built their application with Next.js on their own infrastructure. These are large-scale production applications handling massive traffic on infrastructure that these companies control.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Every major cloud vendor provides Next.js deployment options. Netlify, Cloudflare, AWS Amplify, Google Cloud, and Azure all support Next.js natively. For custom infrastructure setups, open source projects like OpenNext enable Next.js to run with serverless architectures similar to Vercel.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1.5rem;--xs-text-line-height:2rem;--xs-text-weight:600;--xs-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--sm-text-size:1.5rem;--sm-text-line-height:2rem;--sm-text-weight:600;--sm-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--smd-text-size:2rem;--smd-text-line-height:2.5rem;--smd-text-weight:600;--smd-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--md-text-size:2rem;--md-text-line-height:2.5rem;--md-text-weight:600;--md-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--lg-text-size:2rem;--lg-text-line-height:2.5rem;--lg-text-weight:600;--lg-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#next.js-adapters-formalize-the-framework-platform-contract\" id=\"next.js-adapters-formalize-the-framework-platform-contract\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Next.js adapters formalize the framework-platform contract</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Platform providers told us integration was harder than it should be. This is why the <a href=\"https://nextjs.org/blog/next-16#build-adapters-api-alpha\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight\">Next.js team built Build Adapters</a> as explicit versioned APIs to formalize the contract between framework and platform. Adapters define what Next.js outputs, what infrastructure features each route needs, and how platforms should handle them.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Every Next.js 16 application deployed on Vercel uses the same adapter API available to other platforms. Vercel does not have special access or different integration points. The test suite Vercel uses to validate features is available to all platform providers.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">This is part of our broader <a target=\"_self\" data-zone=\"same\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight\" href=\"https://vercel.com/blog/open-sdk-strategy\">Open SDK strategy</a>: building frameworks, SDKs, and tools that are open, portable, and usable on any platform.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1.5rem;--xs-text-line-height:2rem;--xs-text-weight:600;--xs-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--sm-text-size:1.5rem;--sm-text-line-height:2rem;--sm-text-weight:600;--sm-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--smd-text-size:2rem;--smd-text-line-height:2.5rem;--smd-text-weight:600;--smd-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--md-text-size:2rem;--md-text-line-height:2.5rem;--md-text-weight:600;--md-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--lg-text-size:2rem;--lg-text-line-height:2.5rem;--lg-text-weight:600;--lg-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#standards-first,-portable-always\" id=\"standards-first,-portable-always\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Standards first, portable always</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">We prioritize standard protocols wherever possible. Databases offered on the Vercel Marketplace use standard protocols like Postgres and Redis. These are provided through marketplace partners like Neon, Supabase, and Upstash, or you can connect to any instance you operate. AWS is our preferred cloud provider, so when you connect to databases hosted in the same AWS region as your application, you get low-latency connectivity.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">The same philosophy extends to our AI infrastructure. <a href=\"https://vercel.com/ai-gateway\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_self\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight\">AI Gateway </a>supports the OpenAI API format, which has been established as a de-facto industry standard by OpenAI, Anthropic, and most other model providers. Switching between calling OpenAI directly or routing through the AI Gateway requires only changing the API endpoint URL in your configuration, with no code changes needed.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Some services require proprietary APIs because no industry standard exists yet. <a href=\"https://vercel.com/docs/vercel-sandbox\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_self\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight\">Vercel Sandbox</a> provides secure execution of untrusted code. <a href=\"https://vercel.com/docs/edge-config\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_self\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight\">Edge Config</a> offers ultra-low latency reads with a simple <code>get(key)</code> interface for distributed configuration. Moving to alternatives would require updating your code to use their APIs. However, the difference is that these services can be called from any infrastructure, including EC2 or your own servers, without requiring you to use Vercel for hosting. When industry-standard APIs emerge for these use cases, we will implement them.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1.5rem;--xs-text-line-height:2rem;--xs-text-weight:600;--xs-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--sm-text-size:1.5rem;--sm-text-line-height:2rem;--sm-text-weight:600;--sm-text-letter-spacing:-0.96px;--smd-text-size:2rem;--smd-text-line-height:2.5rem;--smd-text-weight:600;--smd-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--md-text-size:2rem;--md-text-line-height:2.5rem;--md-text-weight:600;--md-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px;--lg-text-size:2rem;--lg-text-line-height:2.5rem;--lg-text-weight:600;--lg-text-letter-spacing:-1.28px\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#why-we-build-this-way\" id=\"why-we-build-this-way\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Why we build this way</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">Building portable open source software is a core value at Vercel. We build open source to create an enduring business that enables us to keep developing great open source software. Our goal is to improve the default quality of software for everyone, everywhere, whether they are Vercel customers or not.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">When developers learn Next.js, Nuxt, or the AI SDK, they need to trust that investment won't trap them on a single platform. That trust drives broader adoption. Broader adoption creates a larger ecosystem. A larger ecosystem makes every platform better, including Vercel.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-module__eElGjq__wrapper text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"--text-color:var(--ds-gray-1000);--xs-text-size:1rem;--xs-text-line-height:1.5rem;--xs-text-weight:400;--xs-text-letter-spacing:initial;--sm-text-size:1rem;--sm-text-line-height:1.5rem;--sm-text-weight:400;--sm-text-letter-spacing:initial;--smd-text-size:1rem;--smd-text-line-height:1.5rem;--smd-text-weight:400;--smd-text-letter-spacing:initial;--md-text-size:1rem;--md-text-line-height:1.5rem;--md-text-weight:400;--md-text-letter-spacing:initial;--lg-text-size:1.125rem;--lg-text-line-height:1.5rem;--lg-text-weight:400;--lg-text-letter-spacing:initial\">We want you to stay with Vercel because you choose to, not because you have to. The best way to earn that choice is to build tools that work everywhere and a platform that makes those tools better.</p>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "Vercel 提倡由框架定义的基础设施 (FDI)，防止供应商锁定，强调代码可移植性和开放标准，从而创建一个更健康的开发者生态系统。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "Vercel 提倡由框架定义的基础设施 (FDI)，防止供应商锁定，强调代码可移植性和开放标准，从而创建一个更健康的开发者生态系统。",
  "summary": "文章指出，传统云平台常迫使开发者基于其专有底层组件进行构建，从而造成供应商锁定。为避免这种情况，Vercel 提倡“由框架定义的基础设施”（FDI），即开发者只需按照所选框架（如 Next.js、Remix）编写代码，Vercel 便会自动配置所需的底层基础设施。这种方法确保了代码在各种平台之间的可移植性，简化了本地开发，不再需要平台特定的模拟器，并且与开放标准保持一致。作者强调，已有相当比例的 Next.js 应用程序在 Vercel 之外运行，这证明了 FDI 的实际可移植性。Vercel 还通过 Next.js Build Adapters 和开放 SDK 战略等举措，进一步强化其优先采用标准的理念，并将其扩展到数据库和 AI 网关等服务。Vercel 认为，这一战略有助于建立信任，扩大应用范围，并为所有开发者创建一个更强大的软件生态系统。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "FDI 通过将应用程序代码与专有平台底层组件分离，从而防止供应商锁定。",
      "explanation": "开发者遵循框架的约定进行开发，这确保了应用程序可以在任何支持该框架的基础设施上运行，而不会像使用专有 API 那样将业务逻辑与特定供应商绑定。"
    },
    {
      "point": "FDI 通过消除对平台特定模拟工具的需求，简化了本地开发。",
      "explanation": "开发者使用标准的框架开发服务器，确保本地环境和生产环境行为一致，无需使用复杂的近似模拟工具。"
    },
    {
      "point": "Vercel 对开放标准和框架的承诺，促进了更广泛的生态系统采纳和信任。",
      "explanation": "通过构建开源工具和规范框架与平台之间的合约（例如 Next.js Build Adapters），Vercel 提升了可移植性并建立了信任，使整个开发者社区受益。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
    "云平台可能会通过要求你基于其专有底层组件进行构建来锁定你。Vercel 采用不同的方法：你只需为你使用的框架编写代码，无需为 Vercel 编写。",
    "当平台构建的功能偏离开放标准，并且这些功能通过专有 API 在你的应用程序代码中被调用时，就会发生供应商锁定。",
    "由框架定义的基础设施 (FDI) 意味着平台会读取你的代码，并确定你需要哪些基础设施。你只需遵循框架的模式，剩下的事情由 Vercel 处理。",
    "当你基于框架标准而不是平台底层组件进行开发时，你的代码无需修改即可在其他地方运行。",
    "我们希望你选择继续使用 Vercel，而不是因为你不得不这样做。要赢得用户的选择，最好的方法是构建通用的工具，并提供一个能让这些工具发挥更大作用的平台。"
  ],
